# Language Convention

- English is the project's canonical language: README, docs, code comments,
  commit messages, page metadata and new patch notes (`src/data/changelog.ts`)
  are written in English.
- Portuguese (Brasil) is a player-facing UI locale only. All UI strings live
  in `src/lib/i18n.ts` with both `pt` and `en` dictionaries — never hardcode
  user-visible text in components.
- The app still opens in pt-BR by default (`Locale` default is `'pt'`).
- Old patch notes written in Portuguese are historical documents — do not
  translate them.
- Conversation with the user happens in Portuguese (see user rules), but
  everything committed to the repo is in English.
